# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok the itt corp. is expected to announce , possibly as early as monday , that it has agreed to sell five of its sheraton hotels to felcor suite hotels inc. , a publicly traded real estate investment trust , for $ ### million in cash .
# ::alignments
(e / expect-01
      :ARG1 (a / announce-01
            :ARG0 (c / company
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "ITT"
                        :op2 "Corporation"))
            :ARG1 (a2 / agree-01
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (s / sell-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (h / hotel
                              :quant 5
                              :ARG1-of (ii / include-91
                                    :ARG2 (h2 / hotel
                                          :mod (s2 / sheraton)
                                          :poss c)))
                        :ARG2 (c2 / company
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Felcor"
                                    :op2 "Suite"
                                    :op3 "Hotels"
                                    :op4 "Inc.")
                              :ARG1-of (t / trade-01
                                    :ARG1-of (p / public-02))
                              :ARG0-of (ii2 / invest-01
                                    :ARG2 (r / real-estate)))
                        :ARG3 (m / monetary-quantity
                              :quant 10000000
                              :unit (d / dollar)
                              :mod (c3 / cash))))
            :time (d2 / date-entity
                  :weekday (m2 / monday)
                  :mod (e2 / early))))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok opposition kuomintang -lrb- kmt -rrb- chairman lien chan reiterated his call saturday for a majority of legislators from the opposition `` pan blue alliance '' in the next legislature , in order to safeguard the future course of the republic of china .
# ::alignments

      :ARG0 (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Lien"
                  :op2 "Chan")
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG1 (p2 / political-party
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Kuomintang")
                        :ARG0-of (o / oppose-01))
                  :ARG2 (c / chairman)))
      :ARG1 (c2 / call-03
            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (p3 / person
                  :ARG0-of (l / legislate-01)
                  :quant (m / majority)
                  :ARG0-of (h2 / have-org-role-91
                        :ARG1 (p4 / political-party
                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "Pan"
                                    :op2 "Blue"
                                    :op3 "Alliance")
                              :ARG0-of (o2 / oppose-01))
                        :ARG2 (m2 / member))
                  :location (g / government-organization
                        :ARG0-of (l2 / legislate-01)
                        :mod (n4 / next)))
            :purpose (s / safeguard-01
                  :ARG0 p3
                  :ARG1 (c3 / course
                        :poss (c4 / country
                              :name (n5 / name
                                    :op1 "China"))
                        :time (f / future))))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (s2 / saturday)))

# ::id 2 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

            :mod (j / judiciary))

                        :mod (c / country

                              :ARG3 (j2 / judge-01)))

                        :ARG1 (t / travel-01

                                    :name (n2 / name
                                          :op1 "Moncef"
                                          :op2 "Hussein")
                                    :purpose (r / right-05))
                              :ARG4 (o2 / outside
                                    :op1 (c2 / country)))
                        :ARG2 a3
                        :time (a4 / after
                              :op1 (j3 / jail-01
                                    :ARG1 a3
                                    :time (y / year
                                          :mod (l / last))))))
            :op2 (ii / impose-01
                  :ARG1 (r2 / restrict-01
                        :ARG1 (t2 / travel-01))
                  :time (s3 / subsequent)))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (t3 / thursday)))

                                          :mod (c3 / cruel)
                                          :mod (u / usual
                                                :polarity -)))))))
      :ARG2 ii

            :weekday (t / thursday)))

# ::id 4 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

                        :mod (n / news)
                        :mod (n2 / newspaper

                                    :op1 "New"
                                    :op2 "York"
                                    :op3 "Times")))
                  :ARG2 (c / client)))
      :time (t2 / today))

                              :mod (m / military))

# ::id 8 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

                        :op1 "U.S.")))

            :quant 10
            :unit (d2 / dollar))

            :time "::00"
            :weekday (t2 / tuesday))
      :ARG0-of (c2 / cause-01
            :ARG1 (d4 / down-03
                  :ARG1 (m2 / monetary-quantity
                        :quant 10
                        :unit (d5 / dollar))
                  :time (c3 / close-02
                        :time (d6 / date-entity
                              :weekday (m3 / monday))))))

# ::alignments
(r / return-01
      :ARG1 (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "alex"
                  :op2 "Zanardi")
            :ARG0-of (l / lose-02
                  :ARG1 (l2 / leg
                        :mod (b / both))
                  :ARG1-of (c / cause-01
                        :ARG0 (c2 / crash-01
                              :mod (h / horrific)
                              :time (b2 / before
                                    :op1 (n2 / now)
                                    :quant (t / temporal-quantity
                                          :quant 5
                                          :unit (y / year))))))
            :ARG1-of (h2 / have-part-91
                  :ARG2 (f / formula
                        :mod 1)))
      :ARG4 (t2 / test-01
            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (c3 / car-make
                  :name (n3 / name
                        :op1 "BMW"
                        :op2 "Saver")))
      :time (m / month
            :mod (n4 / next)))

            :op1 (p / point)

            :weekday (m2 / monday)))

# ::alignments
(a / announce-01
      :ARG1 (e / establish-01
            :ARG1 (u / university
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 " chang"))
            :location (c / city
                  :name (n2 / name
                        :op1 "Shanxi")
                  :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                        :ARG1 (n3 / northwest
                              :part-of (p / province
                                    :name (n4 / name
                                          :op1 "China")))
                        :ARG2 (c2 / capital)))
            :ARG0-of (m / merge-01
                  :ARG1 (ii / institution
                        :quant 3
                        :mod (l / learn-01
                              :ARG1-of (h2 / have-degree-91
                                    :ARG2 (h3 / high-02
                                          :ARG1 l)
                                    :ARG3 (m2 / more))))))
      :location (h4 / here)
      :time (t / today))

# ::id 1931 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

# ::alignments
(r / raise-02
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Eliot"
                  :op2 "Spitzer")
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG1 (s / state)
                  :ARG2 (a / attorney
                        :mod (g / general))))
      :ARG1 (m / monetary-quantity
            :quant 1000000
            :unit (d / dollar))
      :time (h2 / half
            :ord (o / ordinal-entity
                  :value 1))
      :purpose (c / campaign-01
            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (b / become-01
                  :ARG1 p
                  :ARG2 (g2 / governor
                        :ARG2-of (h3 / have-org-role-91
                              :ARG0 p
                              :ARG1 s
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "New"
                                    :op2 "York")))))
      :ARG0-of (ii / intensify-01
            :ARG1 (f / fundraise-04
                  :ARG0 p)
            :time (ii2 / in-advance-04
                  :ARG2 (p2 / primary
                        :mod (d2 / democracy)))))

# ::id 1932 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

      :ARG0 (p / person

      :ARG1 (c / close-06
            :ARG1 (s2 / share
                  :ARG1-of (n / new-01))
            :ARG2 (l / low-04
                  :ARG1 s2
                  :ARG2-of (h / have-degree-91
                        :ARG1 s2
                        :ARG3 (m / more
                              :quant (p2 / percentage-entity
                                    :value 1))))
            :time (d2 / date-entity
                  :weekday (m2 / monday))
            :ARG1-of (m3 / mean-01
                  :ARG2 (e / end-01
                        :ARG1 (y / year
                              :ARG1-of (s3 / strong-02))
                        :ARG1-of (q / quiet-04)))))

# ::id 1933 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok european union talks aimed at advancing croatia 's membership have been postponed due to the balkan state 's on-going border row with slovenia , the eu presidency announced thursday .

      :ARG0 (p / presidency
            :mod (o / organization
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "EU")))
      :ARG1 (p2 / postpone-01
            :ARG1 (t / talk-01
                  :ARG0 o
                  :ARG1-of (a2 / aim-02
                        :ARG2 (a3 / advance-01
                              :ARG1 (h / have-org-role-91
                                    :ARG0 o
                                    :ARG1 (c / country
                                          :name (n2 / name
                                                :op1 "Croatia"))
                                    :ARG2 (m / member)))))
            :ARG1-of (c2 / cause-01
                  :ARG0 (r / row-03
                        :ARG0 (s / state
                              :location (w / world-region
                                    :name (n3 / name
                                          :op1 "Balkans")))
                        :ARG1 (c3 / country
                              :name (n4 / name
                                    :op1 "Slovenia"))
                        :ARG2 (b / border)
                        :ARG1-of (g / go-on-15))))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (t2 / thursday)))

# ::id 1934 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

                        :quant (a3 / at-least
                              :op1 6))

                        :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                              :ARG1 (p3 / police
                                    :mod (d / district))
                              :ARG2 (c / commander))))
            :time (c2 / clash-01
                  :time (w / week
                        :mod (l3 / last))
                  :location (n / north
                        :part-of (c3 / country
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Uganda")))))
      :time (t / today))

# ::id 1935 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok mexico 's sporting press cheered two national soccer victories on monday : defeating paraguay #-# in the copa america and beating new zealand #-# in the under-## world cup .

      :ARG0 (p / press

            :poss (c2 / company
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Mexico")))
      :ARG1 (w / win-01
            :quant 2
            :ARG0 c2

                  :mod (n2 / nation))
            :ARG2 (a / and
                  :op1 (d / defeat-01
                        :ARG0 c2
                        :ARG1 (t / team
                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "Paraguay"))
                        :ARG2 (t2 / team
                              :name (n4 / name
                                    :op1 "Premier"
                                    :op2 "and"
                                    :op3 "the"
                                    :op4 "Cup")
                              :mod (c3 / country
                                    :name (n5 / name
                                          :op1 "America"))))
                  :op2 (b / beat-01
                        :ARG0 c2
                        :ARG1 (t3 / team
                              :name (n6 / name
                                    :op1 "New"
                                    :op2 "Lealand"))
                        :ARG2 t2
                        :subevent-of (g / game
                              :name (n7 / name
                                    :op1 "World"
                                    :op2 "Cup")
                              :mod (u / under)))))
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :weekday (m / monday)))

# ::id 1936 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

      :ARG0 (c / country
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "India"))

            :ARG0 (r2 / relation-03
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG2 (c2 / country
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Pakistan")))
            :ARG1 (p / point
                  :ARG1-of (h / have-degree-91
                        :ARG2 (l / low-04
                              :ARG1 p)
                        :ARG3 (m / most)
                        :ARG5 (b / before
                              :op1 (n3 / now)
                              :duration (t / temporal-quantity
                                    :quant 4
                                    :unit (y / year))))))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (f / friday))
      :ARG1-of (r3 / refer-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG2 (t2 / tense-03
                  :ARG1 (a / and
                        :op1 (a2 / attack-01
                              :ARG1 (e / embassy
                                    :mod c
                                    :location (c3 / city
                                          :name (n4 / name
                                                :op1 "Kabul"))))
                        :op2 (e2 / exchange-01
                              :ARG0 (a3 / army
                                    :quant 2)
                              :ARG1 (g / gunfire)
                              :location (r4 / region
                                    :ARG2-of (d2 / dispute-01)
                                    :location (w / world-region
                                          :name (n5 / name
                                                :op1 "Kashmir"))))))
            :ARG1-of (a4 / appear-02)))

# ::id 1942 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

# ::alignments
(e / erupt-01
      :ARG1 (b / battle-01

                  :quant 2
                  :ARG0-of (p / profit-01
                        :polarity -)
                  :ARG0-of (l / lead-01))
            :ARG1-of (s / simmer-01))
      :ARG1-of (p2 / public-02)
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (f / friday))
      :time (s2 / sever-01
            :ARG0 (a / army
                  :mod (s3 / save-02)
                  :mod (s4 / state
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Massachusetts")))
            :ARG1 (t / tie-01
                  :ARG1 a
                  :ARG2 (w / way
                        :ARG1-of (u / unite-01)
                        :mod (b2 / bay
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Massachusetts"
                                    :op2 "Bay"))
                        :mod (v / valley
                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "Merrimack"
                                    :op2 "Valley"))))
            :manner (a2 / abrupt)
            :ARG0-of (e2 / end-01
                  :ARG1 (r / relation-03
                        :ARG0 a
                        :ARG2 o
                        :duration (t2 / temporal-quantity
                              :quant 1
                              :unit (y / year))))))
